From: Mike Snitzer <snitzer@kernel.org>
Date: Thu, 16 Feb 2023 15:29:44 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] dm thin: add cond_resched() to various workqueue loops
Git-commit: e4f80303c2353952e6e980b23914e4214487f2a6
Patch-mainline: v6.3-rc1
References: git-fixes

Otherwise on resource constrained systems these workqueues may be too
greedy.

Signed-off-by: Mike Snitzer <snitzer@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Coly Li <colyli@suse.de>

---
 drivers/md/dm-thin.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/md/dm-thin.c b/drivers/md/dm-thin.c
index affd91a53042..6cd105c1cef3 100644
--- a/drivers/md/dm-thin.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-thin.c
@@ -2209,6 +2209,7 @@ static void process_thin_deferred_bios(struct thin_c *tc)
 			throttle_work_update(&pool->throttle);
 			dm_pool_issue_prefetches(pool->pmd);
 		}
+		cond_resched();
 	}
 	blk_finish_plug(&plug);
 }
@@ -2291,6 +2292,7 @@ static void process_thin_deferred_cells(struct thin_c *tc)
 			else
 				pool->process_cell(tc, cell);
 		}
+		cond_resched();
 	} while (!list_empty(&cells));
 }
 
